**Mission:** Full parse colosseum-dashboard/data/email_colosseum.json leaderboard (45 beings) → UPSERT ALL into email_ad.db (id, type, content, wins, losses, score, generation, created_at, parent_id=null).

**Backup:** cp email_ad.db email_ad.pre_full.bak

**UPSERT:** INSERT OR REPLACE INTO beings (id, type, content, wins, losses, score, generation, created_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET wins=excluded.wins, losses=excluded.losses, score=excluded.score, content=excluded.content;

**Post-ingest Proofs:**
1. SELECT COUNT(*) FROM beings;
2. SELECT MIN(id), MAX(id), COUNT(*) FROM beings;
3. SELECT type, COUNT(*) GROUP BY type;
4. SELECT id, type, wins, losses, LENGTH(content) FROM beings WHERE id IN (1,6,9,13,15,20,21,22,23,24,30,34,35,38,39,40,41,42,43,44,45) ORDER BY id;

**Update:** rankings.json with new stats.

cd colosseum-dashboard. Use sqlite3 exec.

